    <div class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Interstellar</strong> is a science fiction epic that blends emotional storytelling with hard science. In a future where Earth is becoming uninhabitable, a former NASA pilot, Cooper, joins a mission to travel through a wormhole in search of a new home for humanity. The film tackles concepts of time dilation, black holes, love, and the survival instinct.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Main Cast</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Matthew McConaughey as Cooper</li>
        <li>Anne Hathaway as Dr. Amelia Brand</li>
        <li>Jessica Chastain as Murph</li>
        <li>Michael Caine as Professor Brand</li>
        <li>Mackenzie Foy as Young Murph</li>
        <li>Casey Affleck as Tom Cooper</li>
        <li>Matt Damon as Dr. Mann</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Themes & Impact</h2>
      <p>
        Interstellar explores deep scientific theories like relativity and quantum gravity while grounding them in emotional themes of family, sacrifice, and endurance. Hans Zimmerâ€™s haunting score and the breathtaking visuals make the film a modern masterpiece.
        It has inspired scientists and artists alike, and its portrayal of a black hole helped inform real scientific visualizations.
      </p>
